def: Of or pertaining to the middle division of the Tertiary.-- n.
A kind of seedless raisin produced near Smyrna in AsiaticTurkey. Sultana bird (Zo√∂l.), the hyacinthine, or purple, gallinule.See Illust. under Gallinule.
Of or pertaining to the southwest; southwesterly; as, to sail asouthwestern course.
To plant or set in a tub; as, to tub a plant.
Serving as an antidote.-- An`ti*dot"ic*al*ly, adv.
Having the nose of medium width; between leptorhine andplatyrhine.
Given to tricks; practicing deception; trickish; knavish.
A kind of pleasure carriage; a coach. [Obs.]To mount two-wheeled caroches. Butler.

A plant of the genus Iris (I. Florentina); a kind of flower-de-luce. Its rootstock has an odor resembling that of violets. Orris pea(Med.), an issue pea made from orris root.-- Orris root, the fragrant rootstock of the orris.
